
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-fairhurst-tsvwg-6man-udpzero-02.txt'>
    <title>"IPv6 UDP Checksum Considerations", Gorry Fairhurst, Magnus Westerlund</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-fairhurst-tsvwg-6man-udpzero-02.txt</link>
    <description>This document examines the role of the transport checksum when used with IPv6, as defined in RFC2460.  It presents a summary of the trade-offs for evaluating the safety of updating RFC 2460 to permit an IPv6 UDP endpoint to use a zero value in the checksum field to indicate that no checksum is present.  The document describes issues and design principles that need to be considered and provides recommendations.</description>
    <dc:date>2010-03-21T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
